# ES6 Arrow Functions

In 2015, JavaScript got a massive update called ES6. One of the biggest additions was the **Arrow Function**.

Arrow functions do the exact same thing as standard functions, but with less typing! Programmers love them because they look sleek and modern.

```javascript
// Traditional Object
function addNumber(a, b) {
  return a + b;
}
```

Take off the `function` keyword, save it in a `const` variable, and add a "fat arrow" `=>`.

slides.codeSnippet:
const doubleScore = (score) => score * 2;

const isAdult = (age) => age >= 18;

console.log("Double 50 is: ", doubleScore(50));
console.log("Is 21 an adult?: ", isAdult(21));
